.TH man 3 "May 29, 2023" "9.15" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
.B _printf
- A simplified version of the printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
To use this function, include the "main.h" header file
.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf function generates output based on a specified format.
The output is written to the standard output stream, which is typically the terminal.
.SH USAGE
To use _printf you have to use the following key characters preceeded by % symbol.
.RS 3
%c: Used to print characters
.RS 0
%s: Used to print strings
.RS 0
%d: Used to print integers with the maximum and minimum size of an int type
.RS 0
%i: Used to print integers with the maximum and minimum size of an int type
.RS 0
%b: Used to print a number in binary form
.SH RETURN VALUES
The _printf function returns an integer indicating the number of symbols printed,
excluding the null terminator (\0) for strings.
.SH SEE ALSO
.I printf(3)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
Chtistabel Aidoo, and Philipa Aidoo
